Validations.
    - AngularJS By Default Supports Form Validations.

    - Angular Framework Stores the , Form Related Errors into "$error" object.


Text Validation.
-
<form name="myForm">
    <input type="text"
           name="uname"
           ng-model="uname"
           ng-minlength="3"
           ng-maxlength="6"
           required>

    <div ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.minlength">***Minimum 3 Characters Are Required***</div>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.maxlength">****Maximum 6 Characters Are Allowed***</div>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.required">****Can't Left Blank***</div>
</form>


Email Validation.
-
<form name="myForm">

    <input type="email"
           name="uemail"
           ng-model="uemail"
           required>

    <div ng-if="myForm.uemail.$error.email">****Please Enter the Valid Email****</div>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uemail.$error.required">****Can't Left Blank****</div>

</form>



Phone Number Validation / Number Validation
-
<form name="myForm">
    <input type="text"
           name="uphone"
           ng-model="uphone"
           ng-pattern="/^\d{0,9}(\.\d{1,9})?$/"
           required>

    <div ng-if="myForm.uphone.$error.required">****Can't Left Blank****</div>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uphone.$error.pattern">****Please Enter The Valid Phone Number****</div>
</form>




Validations by using ngMessages Module
-

    - ngMessages Module used to overcome the "duplicate Validation Messages" in angular applications.

Ex.
    var app = angular.module("app",["ngMessages"]);


Text Validation.
-
<form name="myForm">
    <input type="text"
           name="uname"
           ng-model="uname"
           ng-minlength="3"
           ng-maxlength="6"
           required>

    <div ng-messages="myForm.uname.$error">
        <div ng-message="minlength">****Minimum 3 Characters are Required****</div>
        <div ng-message="maxlength">****Maximum 6 Characters are Allowed****</div>
        <div ng-message="required">****Can't Left Blank****</div>
    </div>

</form>




































